<item>
            <title>[SPR-3202] form:errors tag does not render in freemarker view</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-3202</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using Freemarkers TagLib-Support to make use of spring form tags in freemarker views.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example: page.ftl&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;#assign form=JspTaglibs&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;http://www.springframework.org/tags/form&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;@form.form commandName=&quot;registrationData&quot; method=&quot;post&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	...&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;@form.errors path=&quot;surname&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;/@form.form&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;All tags render fine except for the ErrorsTag. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Debugging through the code, I can see that ErrorsTag.renderDefaultContent is successfully processed and finds the errors, but it doesn&apos;t show up in the generated HTML.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
